dcterms:description: The ADHD-200 dataset consists of resting-state functional magnetic resonance imaging (rs-fMRI) images of 973 subjects, including healthy individuals and those diagnosed with ADHD. It is used to investigate brain connectivity networks and their development over age.
dcterms:title: ADHD-200 dataset
